courier (1.1.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Batch-first JSON output: all commands now wrap results under an operation
    key {"search from:x": {"account": {...}}} — breaking change for 1.0.x
    consumers that parsed the account name as the top-level key.
  * New `batch` subcommand: accepts multiple operation strings (as args,
    --file, or stdin JSON array) and executes all ops per account over a
    single IMAP connection, eliminating per-query reconnect overhead.
  * `read` output now uses the same batch JSON shape as `search`.
  * `status` and `mcp --version` now derive version from __version__ instead
    of a hardcoded string.

 -- Weiwu Zhang <a@colourful.land>  Tue, 28 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000

courier (1.0.3) unstable; urgency=medium

  * search: AI-friendly CLI compat. Soft-redirect of search-variant subcommand
    names (email_search, email-search, search_email, search-email) to 'search'
    with a stderr note. Accept --account/-a both before and after the
    subcommand. Add --query/-q as alias for the positional query.
  * search: fix Gmail default-folder failure. list_folders now skips
    \\Noselect / \\NonExistent entries, so the [Gmail] parent no longer enters
    the folder list. When --folder is omitted, prefer the SPECIAL-USE \\All
    folder (Gmail's [Gmail]/All Mail, Fastmail's Archive, etc.) — one SELECT
    instead of iterating every folder.
  * search: multi-account support. --account/-a accepted multiply;
    --all-accounts/-A searches every configured account. Output is now
    always nested by account name ({"acct": {...}}) — breaking change
    for consumers that previously parsed a flat array. --limit applies
    per account.
  * search: optional local-cache backend via mu (Xapian).  When a
    [local_cache] block is configured and an account names a maildir,
    the search MCP tool and CLI command serve from `mu find` over a
    subprocess instead of IMAP, with transparent fallback on stale,
    untranslatable, or folder-scoped queries.  Every search response
    now wraps {"results", "provenance"}; provenance reports the source,
    indexed_at, and any fall-back reason.  This is a breaking change
    in result shape for consumers that indexed the bare result list.
  * search: route Gmail header queries (from:/to:/cc:/bcc:) through
    X-GM-RAW.  Standard IMAP `SEARCH TO foo@bar` against Gmail's All
    Mail did not filter by header for values containing "@"/"."; the
    X-GM-RAW dispatch evaluates with web-UI semantics and filters
    correctly.

  * search/read: surface message_id, in_reply_to, and references.  IMAP
    remote search now emits message_id in every result dict (parity with
    the local-cache path).  The read command emits message_id always and
    in_reply_to/references when non-empty.  --format text appends an
    "id:" line per hit; --format oneline appends message_id as a trailing
    tab column.

 -- Weiwu Zhang <a@colourful.land>  Sun, 26 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000

